result.formatted_address: 35 Amoy St, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: The Spice House Restaurant

reviews.text: As soon as we entered the restaurant the service was inattentive and unwelcoming. We read previous reviews on this restaurant and realised that the quality of food has gone downhill in the last couple of years. We decided to give it a go anyway. TRUST THE REVIEWS. The food is absolutely horrible tastes bad and is overpriced. Honestly felt sick and unsatisfied after leaving half of the food on the plate.  Especially the fried rice. There are WAY better Thai places in Hong Kong for cheaper prices.

The first time to be here & curious to try given the queue outside even before it opened for lunch. Staff were Thai people whereby I think the food should be authentic. However, it was big disappointment when the food & drink arrived. Simply it tasted not good. Bye bye.

Hit or miss. The omelet pad thai is really good. Well seasoned, tasty noodles, fast and delicious. The curry fried rice is seriously iffy. Overly fishy. Filled with rock hard dried peas (I hope). It has earned its hidden gem status, but too many dishes have unpleasant aspects.

My friend and I had dinner tonight. We had Chicken in coconut milk soup, Steam rice, Mango Salad and stir fried minced pork with chilli and basil on rice. The food is not as good as before the staff are not nice and to our big surprise they charged us a Tom
yum Prawn which we didn’t have! Quite disappointed ☹️ Better check your bill when your paying

Had tom yum soup noodle and iced lemon tea on lunch set menu. My friend had curry soup noodle. My soup was nice but I think my friend’s curry soup had more flavour. Staff nice, good location, queues at lunch time which I managed to avoid by getting there just before 12:30. I would go back for a quick lunch if there is no queue. Would recommend to my friends.
